#Frontend Developer Intern Assignment
This project is part of the assignment for the Frontend Developer Intern position. It consists of two main parts:

1.Next.js Web App: A Google Sign-In website using Firebase Auth and Material-UI.

2.Expo Mobile App: A mobile app that loads the web app using WebView and integrates Firebase Cloud Messaging (FCM) for push notifications.

#Next.js Web App with Google Sign-In
.Start the app using:npm run dev
.The app will be running on http://localhost:3000.
.Login using Google Auth. Upon successful login, users will be redirected to the /home page.

#Expo Mobile App with WebView
.To run the app locally:npx expo start.
.Scan the QR code with the Expo Go app on your mobile device.
.The Expo app will load the Next.js web app in a WebView and allow Google Sign-In.

#Push Notifications (FCM):
.Firebase Cloud Messaging (FCM) is integrated for push notifications.
.To enable push notifications, ensure Firebase setup is completed and google-services.json is added to the android/app/ folder.

###Send Notification from Firebase
->Go to Firebase Console.

->Select your project â†’ Click Cloud Messaging.

->Click Send Your First Message.

->Enter a Title and Body.

->Choose Send via device token.

->Paste the FCM token from your app.

->Listen for incoming notifications.

#Technologies Used
*Frontend: Next.js, React.js, Material-UI (MUI)

*Authentication: Firebase Google Auth

*Push Notifications: Firebase Cloud Messaging (FCM)

*Mobile: React Native, Expo, WebView

#Deploy the Web App

push to Netlify

#Deploy the Mobile App

Use EAS Build:eas build -p android

